ndows.Forms.ListView.CheckBoxes%2A>  \\n  \\n-   <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListView.FullRowSelect%2A>  \\n  \\n-   <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListView.GridLines%2A>  \\n  \\n-   <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListView.Sorting%2A>  \\n  \\n This example requires that you have added the code to a <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Form> and call the method created in the example from the constructor or another method on the form. The example also requires that images named `MySmallImage1`, `MySmallImage2`, `MyLargeImage1`, and `MyLargeImage2` are located in the root directory of drive C.  \\n  \\n [!code-cpp[ListViewExample#1](~/add/codesnippet/cpp/p-system.windows.forms.l_88_1.cpp)]\\n [!code-cs[ListViewExample#1](~/add/codesnippet/csharp/p-system.windows.forms.l_88_1.cs)]\\n [!code-vb[ListViewExample#1](~/add/codesnippet/visualbasic/p-system.windows.forms.l_88_1.vb)]\"\n  syntax:\n    content: public bool AllowColumnReorder { get; set; }\n    return:\n      type: System.Boolean\n      description: <xref uid=\"langword_csharp_true\" name=\"true\" href=\"\"></xref> if drag-and-drop column reordering is allowed; otherwise, <xref uid=\"langword_csharp_false\" name=\"false\" href=\"\"></xref>. The default is <xref uid=\"langword_csharp_false\" name=\"false\" href=\"\"></xref>.\n  overload: System.Windows.Forms.ListView.AllowColumnReorder*\n  exceptions: []\n  platform:\n  - net462\n- uid: System.Windows.Forms.ListView.ArrangeIcons\n  id: ArrangeIcons\n  parent: System.Windows.Forms.ListView\n  langs:\n  - csharp\n  name: ArrangeIcons()\n  nameWithType: ListView.ArrangeIcons()\n  fullName: System.Windows.Forms.ListView.ArrangeIcons()\n  type: Method\n  assemblies:\n  - System.Windows.Forms\n  namespace: System.Windows.Forms\n  summary: Arranges items in the control when they are displayed as icons based on the value of the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListView.Alignment*> property.\n  remarks: The <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListView.ArrangeIcons%2A> method is only useful when the <xre