 the parameter will return the item whose text is \\\"bracket\\\".  \\n  \\n The <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListView.FindItemWithText%2A> method returns `null` if the list is empty or there is no matching item.\"\n  syntax:\n    content: public System.Windows.Forms.ListViewItem FindItemWithText (string text, bool includeSubItemsInSearch, int startIndex);\n    parameters:\n    - id: text\n      type: System.String\n      description: The text to search for.\n    - id: includeSubItemsInSearch\n      type: System.Boolean\n      description: <xref uid=\"langword_csharp_true\" name=\"true\" href=\"\"></xref> to include subitems in the search; otherwise, <xref uid=\"langword_csharp_false\" name=\"false\" href=\"\"></xref>.\n    - id: startIndex\n      type: System.Int32\n      description: The index of the item at which to start the search.\n    return:\n      type: System.Windows.Forms.ListViewItem\n      description: The first <xref href=\"System.Windows.Forms.ListViewItem\"></xref> that begins with the specified text value.\n  overload: System.Windows.Forms.ListView.FindItemWithText*\n  exceptions:\n  - type: System.ArgumentOutOfRangeException\n    commentId: T:System.ArgumentOutOfRangeException\n    description: <code>startIndex</code> is less 0 or more than the number items in the <xref href=\"System.Windows.Forms.ListView\"></xref>.\n  platform:\n  - net462\n- uid: System.Windows.Forms.ListView.FindItemWithText(System.String,System.Boolean,System.Int32,System.Boolean)\n  id: FindItemWithText(System.String,System.Boolean,System.Int32,System.Boolean)\n  parent: System.Windows.Forms.ListView\n  langs:\n  - csharp\n  name: FindItemWithText(String,Boolean,Int32,Boolean)\n  nameWithType: ListView.FindItemWithText(String,Boolean,Int32,Boolean)\n  fullName: System.Windows.Forms.ListView.FindItemWithText(String,Boolean,Int32,Boolean)\n  type: Method\n  assemblies:\n  - System.Windows.Forms\n  namespace: System.Windows.Forms\n  summary: Finds the first <xref href=\"System.Windows.Forms.ListViewItem\"></xref> or <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListViewItem.ListViewSubItem>, if indicated, that begins with the specified text value. The search starts at the specified index.\n  remarks: \"The <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListView.FindItemWithText%2A> method returns `null` if the list is empty or there is no matching item.  \\n  \\n The search is case-insensitive.  \\n  \\n The `text` parameter can specify a substring of the desired matching text. This method will return the first item that starts with the specified text, unless `false` is passed in for `isPrefixSearch`. For example, if a <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListView> contains two list items—the first item's text set to \\\"angle bracket\\\" and the second item's text set to \\\"bracket\\\"—a call to <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListView.FindItemWithText%2A> passing \\\"brack\\\" as the search text will return the item whose text is \\\"bracket\\\". If `isPrefixSearch` is set to `false`, this call will return `null`.\"\n  syntax:\n    content: public System.Windows.Forms.ListViewItem FindItemWithText (string text, bool includeSubItemsInSearch, int startIndex, bool isPrefixSearch);\n    parameters:\n    - id: text\n      type: System.String\n      description: The text to search for.\n    - id: includeSubItemsInSearch\n      type: System.Boolean\n      description: <xref uid=\"langword_csharp_true\" name=\"true\" href=\"\"></xref> to include subitems in the search; otherwise, <xref uid=\"langword_csharp_false\" name=\"false\" href=\"\"></xref>.\n    - id: startIndex\n      type: System.Int32\n      description: The index of the item at which to start the search.\n    - id: isPrefixSearch\n      type: System.Boolean\n      description: <xref uid=\"langword_csharp_true\" name=\"true\" href=\"\"></xref> to allow partial matches; otherwise, <xref uid=\"langword_csharp_false\" name=\"false\" href=\"\"></xref>.\n    return:\n      type: System.Windows.Forms.ListViewItem\n      description: The first <xref href=\"System.Windows.Forms.ListViewItem\"></xref> that begins with the specified text value.\n  overload: System.Windows.Forms.ListView.FindItemWithText*\n  exceptions:\n  - type: System.ArgumentOutOfRangeException\n    commentId: T:System.ArgumentOutOfRangeException\n    description: <code>startIndex</code> is less than 0 or more than the number of items in the <xref href=\"System.Windows.Forms.ListView\"></xref>.\n  platform:\n  - net462\n- uid: System.Windows.Forms.ListView.FindNearestItem(System.Windows.Forms.SearchDirectionHint,System.Drawing.Point)\n  id: FindNearestItem(System.Windows.Forms.SearchDirectionHint,System.Drawing.Point)\n  parent: System.Windows.Forms.ListView\n  langs:\n  - csharp\n  name: FindNearestItem(SearchDirectionHint,Point)\n  nameWithType: ListView.FindNearestItem(SearchDirectionHint,Point)\n  fullName: System.Windows.Forms.ListView.FindNearestItem(SearchDirectionHint,Point)\n  type: Method\n  assemblies:\n  - System.Windows.Forms\n  namespace: System.Windows.Forms\n  summary: Finds the next item from the given point, searching in the specified direction\n  remarks: The <xref:System.Windows.Forms.ListView.FindNearestItem%2A> method returns `null` if no item is found in the given direction. Identifying the nearest item can vary depending on the operating system the application is running on, and will affect the results of FindNearestItem.\n  syntax:\n    content: public System.Windows.Forms.ListViewItem FindNearestItem (System.Windows.Forms.SearchDirectionHint dir, System.Drawing.Point point);\n    parameters:\n    - id: dir\n      type: System.Windows.Forms.SearchDirectionHint\n      description: One of the <xref href=\"System.Windows.Forms.SearchDirectionHint\"></xref> values.\n    - id: point\n      type: System.Drawing.Point\n      description: The point at which to begin searching.\n    return:\n      type: System.Windows.Forms.ListViewItem\n      description: The <xref href=\"System.Windows.Forms.ListViewItem\"></xref> that is